Since \overset {\leftarrow }{\mathcal  L} (\mathcal  C) is constructed as the total category of an indexed category

\overset {\leftarrow }{\mathcal  L} (\mathcal  C) = \int _{X : \mathcal  C} \mathcal  C [X]^\mathrm {op}

it is equipped with a fibration \mathbb  F : \overset {\leftarrow }{\mathcal  L} (\mathcal  C) \to  \mathcal  C called the forwards fibration.

Since \overset {\leftarrow }{\mathcal  L} (\mathcal  C) is constructed as the total category of an indexed category

\overset {\leftarrow }{\mathcal  L} (\mathcal  C) = \int _{X : \mathcal  C} \mathcal  C [X]^\mathrm {op}

it is equipped with a fibration \mathbb  F : \overset {\leftarrow }{\mathcal  L} (\mathcal  C) \to  \mathcal  C called the forwards fibration.
